    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Correction of June 4 article about refinancing car loans that misstated some aspects of a five-year, $38,000 loan at 10 percent interest (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>An article last Sunday about refinancing car loans misstated some aspects of a five-year, $38,000 loan at 10 percent interest. After making payments for one year, the borrower would owe $31,833 principal on the loan, not $38,736. An average of 39 percent of the first-year payment amount, not a majority, is applied to interest on such a loan.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
